
# mdadm allows you to create RAID arrays with block devices. 

mdadm 

# mkfs allows you to create filesystems on top of a block device.

mkfs.<fs>

# fdisk allows you to update the partition tables for block devices.

fdisk

# parted is another tool to update partition tables on disks.

parted

# cryptsetup allows you to configure LUKS on block devices.

cryptsetup

## LVM management stuff.

# pv<create|display|resize|s|remove|...> is for managing physical volumes with your system.

# vg<create|diaply|remove|...> is for managing volume groups within your system.

# lv<create|extend|remove|display> is for managing logical volumes that are built from volume groups.
